> Pork chops are always a weeknight winner. They're satisfying, speedy, and so versatile,
> which is why our chefs are always brainstorming new ways to take 'em to the next
> level. The kicker this week: a fresh ginger and apricot jam pan sauce. On the side,
> there's crisp roasted green beans and a bed of buttery jasmine rice (perfect for
> catching any runoff sauce). Prepare for a flavor explosion.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add half the ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a drizzle of oil and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

== Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @apricot jam{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and
1/4 cup water.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add remaining ginger
and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in jam mixture and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt
and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with salt
and pepper.

Divide rice and green beans between plates. Top rice with pork and drizzle with
sauce. Garnish with chili to taste and serve.